\insrsid5911984 The former became blind, in consequence of his sickness, but instinctively found his way to the ocean's shore, where, recovering h
is health, he, for many years, was the most notable object that met the eye of the visitor or traveler at San Pedro. He was unfortunately drowned, by falling from a steep bank into the ocean. The latter lived, for many years, in the family of one of our m
ost respectable citizens, in whose care she was at the time of her death. {\*\atrfstart 398026108}The solitary female that was left on the Island, in consequence of her flight from those who brought away her relatives, remained there in regal solitude}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid5515365 {\*\atrfend 398026108}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 398026108}{\*\atndate -953705508}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar
\s16\ql \li0\ri0\sa160\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs15\fs16\insrsid5515365 \chatn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid83818 Indian Queen}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5911984 
. She was frequently seen by the hunters who visited the Island and in subsequent years, but all efforts to hold communication with her were unsuccessful, as she invariably fled from the approach of every human eye.
\par 
\par About 1853 or 1856, Mr. Georg
e Niedeever, who, for many years, had been engaged in otter hunting, and had frequently visited the Island, found her, old, infirm, and decrepid, suffering from hunger, and succeeded in removing her from her solitary and lonesome abode.
\par 
\par {\*\atrfstart 398026109}The Santa Barbara <i>Gazette</i> remarks that this hapless woman had lost the knowledge of language, and that all that was known of her history while living on the island, was ascertained by her signs and gestures. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid5515365 {\*\atrfend 398026109}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 398026109}{\*\atndate -953705508}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar
